      "content": "I hear that you're feeling frustrated, but it's vital to understand that warfarin is a carefully calibrated medication, and any interruption or alteration can increase the risk of serious complications. Tapering off warfarin without medical supervision can lead to unstable blood clots or bleeding. If you're eager to explore natural alternatives and feel your concerns are not being heard, you might consider seeking a second opinion from another healthcare provider. They might offer new insights or be more receptive to discussing your desire to modify your treatment plan. Safety must always be the top priority.",
